jobContext:
Demonstrate a current understanding of curriculum across MYP, DP, WACE, and curriculum initiatives at AusIS;
Guide students and teachers in their reading choices;
Maintain and update the digital library system;
Responsible for the overall management of the Library;
Linkage for new resources and maintain current resources;
Maintain full and working knowledge of library software;
Ensure Current Awareness Service (CAS);
Assist students in selecting and referencing materials for the task ahead;
Making the library engaged in using media programmes;
Providing a supporting role to the IB MYP and DP programme for personal learning and projects;
Promote the use of the library for whole-school teaching and learning; 
Ensure books and resources are well organized and up to date; 
Planning and deploying library-based lessons; 
Have clear policies and procedures that are updated in the library;
Establish behavioral standards in the library;
Ensure the library is clean and tidy and is a safe learning environment; 
Have an insight into budgeting for the library; 
Attend staff meetings and work closely with the senior management team; 
Promote the library resources and reading by inviting authors, organizing book weeks;
Use selection tools / reviewing journals to keep informed about current children's literature
Provide informal one-on-one support to teachers regarding resources in a variety of formats and strategies for their use;
Work with Coordinators, class teachers, and specialist teachers to support curriculum innovations at AusIS;
Maintain a collection of current professional resources for teachers including
online access to journals;
Follow AusIS procedures for circulation and the processing of new resources;
Work with the other AusIS Teacher-librarian to create a Collection;
Use reviewing journals to keep up-to-date on new titles;
Identify gaps in the collection for new purchases and replacement;
Identify gaps in the collection and select resources accordingly;
Prepare resource orders;
Indexing using technology; 
Manage inventory system;
Comfortable with handling audio-visual materials;
Organize Book Week and Book Fair
Conduct the library classes;
Prepares lesson plan and daily plan according to the theme;
Knows the learning capabilities of individual students;
Provides individual and collaborative learning opportunities;
Uses DOTT time efficiently for a planning meetings with parents and administrative tasks;
Assess the children's reading level by doing the running record;
Run the reading intervention program;
